Robert Dartois https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Dartois 0 Robert Dartois (11 February 1900 – 13 January 1959) was a French actor. In 1948 he starred in the film The Lame Devil under Sacha Guitry. He was born Robert Edouard Marcel Delandres in Trouville-sur-Mer, Calvados, France and died in Saint-Arnoult, Calvados, France.
